The price-earnings ratio (P/E Ratio) is the ratio for valuing a company that measures its current share price relative to its per-share earnings.
The price-to-book ratio (P/B Ratio) is a ratio used to compare a stock's market value to its book value, the value at which an asset is carried on its balance sheet).





